   Date: Wed, 15 Feb 89 09:37:41 EST
   From: hubcap@hubcap.clemson.edu (Mike Marshall)

   Rick Adams muses:
    * What would be the proper domain name for something like MCImail or
    * Compuserve's Information Service or Easylink?
    * 
   Well, it seems to me that the typical person using such a service might
   be Joe Blow, an accountant from Nassau, NY.

   His mail box should be jblow@acc.nassau.ny.us, and if he uses MCImail, he
   should arrange for MCI to have an MX record for acc.nassau.ny.us on
   their Internet host mci.com (I know there probably isn't such a host).

I thought of this also, but it doesn't work.  Consider two such people
from the same neck of the woods - one on MCI and one on Compuserve.
There would be only one MX record and it would point to the wrong host
for at least one of these poor souls.  The distinguishing part of the
address (the person name) is on the wrong side of the "@".

Mail-alias@jblow.acc.nassau.ny.us with an MX record and the
appropriate software reading the mail for mail-alias would work I
guess.  But what a grungy hack....

Hmm...is it too late to throw away our at-signs?
stjohns.beast.ddn.mil vs stjohns@beast.ddn.mil?

Mike

